That the Creator might have produced the whole by a single and instantaneous effort, is not to be denied 3 but, as both revelation and nature concur in asserting that such was not the fact, it is no more derogatory to him, with whom a thousand years are but as one day, and one day as a thousand yearS, to suppose that he allotted six thousand years to the completion of his design than that he executed it in six days. And, surely, there is something far more magnificent in conceiving the world to have progressively attain- ed form, order, and vitality, from the mere operation of powers communi- cated to it in a sta-te of chaos, or unfashioned matter, than in sup- posing the actual and persevering exertions of the Almighty for a de·- finite, although a shorter period of time ⁸4.
